@NODE "limits" "Limitations of unregistered version"

Only few limitations of the program:

1. All load/save of program preferences.
2. Inserts "UNREGISTERED" string in programs output.

For more information read @{"History" LINK "history"}.
To register go "@{"Registration" LINK "Registration"}".

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Use" "Short Instructions"

Start the program. Select the drawer with pictures or html documents. Sorry but the program
did not check for the presence of pictures- It will generate empty html
document.
Press "Begin Generatig" button. Your generated index file appears in
the same drawer as all the source pictures. 
Use any web browser to test the results. I'll not describe all the features
of the program. The best way to knew them is to test! You'll not destroy
anything...(I think)
(Some of the features may be not working on particular browser. Use IBrowse
or Voyager for the best result)
If you use 'Batch process' - you need to run Rexx and some Image processing
program. For more info go @{"Script" LINK "Script"} configuration.

If you hate MUI or you are CLI maniac, use @{"CLI" LINK "CLI"} version!

Best wishes!


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Script" "How to use external script"
@TOC "MAIN"

You can use external Rexx script to manipulate external image processing
program. Included scipt "scale.rex" is used with :

  Image Engineer V2.1
   by Simon Edwards
       2/10/95

Copyright © 1995 Simon Edwards. All rights reserved
Email: s9407349@yallara.cs.rmit.edu.au
Freely Distributable

I use this program because it is free. Author release some V3.X version, but
it didn't work with my Amiga.
I think that included script must work with all versions of image engineer.

Or use script by Matthias Finger <matthias.finger@tu-clausthal.de>,
it is used with GfxCON (Aminet: gfx/conv).


You can program your script and use with other programs. (I will be very
pleased if someone could send me the scripts. I'll include them in other
archyves)



In MUI text gadget you can place various commands and parameters:

These magic tokens will help you:

%s - source file
%p - path to source file
%d - destination drawer
%x - icon X size (width)
%y - icon Y size (height)

new from version (2.18)

%c - percents of scale
%w - real width of the picture
%h - real height of the picture

For example is source file is "nice-girl.jpg", path is "Ram Disk:temp/":

"%p%s"     = "Ram Disk:temp/nice-girl.jpg"
"%p%d/%s"  = "Ram Disk:temp/iconeles/nice-girl.jpg"

and

c:RX Rexx:scale.rex "%p%s" "%p%d/%s" %x %y

= c:RX Rexx:scale.rex "Ram Disk:temp/nice-girl.jpg" "Ram
Disk:temp/iconeles/nice-girl.jpg" 100 50

And this command will call Rexx script which generates thunbnail of image
and place in special "iconeles" drawer with the same name as original
picture.

If you have cool Amiga with lots of memory and fast CPU add:
"RUN >NIL:"
in the beginnig of Rexx script.

Running this script Amiga will generate few simultanious processes.

The whole script will look like this:
run >NIL: c:RX Rexx:scale.rex "%p%s" "%p%d/%s" %x %y

@ENDNODE
